%N A368091 Triangle read by rows. T(n, k) = Sum_{p in P(n, k)} Product_{r in p} r, where P(n, k) are the partitions of n with length k.
%H A368091 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A368091/b368091.txt">Rows n = 0..200, flattened</a>
%F A368091 Sum_{k=0..n} (-1)^k * T(n,k) = A022693(n). - _Alois P. Heinz_, Mar 10 2026
%e A368091 Triangle T(n, k) starts:
%e A368091   [0] [1]
%e A368091   [1] [0, 1]
%e A368091   [2] [0, 2,  1]
%e A368091   [3] [0, 3,  2,   1]
%e A368091   [4] [0, 4,  7,   2,  1]
%e A368091   [5] [0, 5, 10,   7,  2,  1]
%e A368091   [6] [0, 6, 22,  18,  7,  2,  1]
%e A368091   [7] [0, 7, 28,  34, 18,  7,  2, 1]
%e A368091   [8] [0, 8, 50,  62, 50, 18,  7, 2, 1]
%e A368091   [9] [0, 9, 60, 121, 86, 50, 18, 7, 2, 1]
%e A368091   ...
%p A368091 b:= proc(n, i) option remember; expand(`if`(n=0, 1,
%p A368091       add(x^j*b(n-i*j, i-1)*(i^j), j=`if`(i=1, n, 0..n/i))))
%p A368091     end:
%p A368091 T:= n-> (p-> seq(coeff(p, x, i), i=0..degree(p)))(b(n$2)):
%p A368091 seq(T(n), n=0..11);  # _Alois P. Heinz_, Mar 10 2026
%o A368091 (SageMath)
%o A368091 def T(n, k):
%o A368091     return sum(product(r for r in p) for p in Partitions(n, length=k))
%o A368091 for n in range(10): print([T(n, k) for k in range(n + 1)])
%Y A368091 Columns k=0..3 give: A000007, A000027, A023855(n-1), A307684.
%Y A368091 Row sums give A006906.
%Y A368091 T(2n,n) gives A074141.
%Y A368091 Cf. A022693, A368090, A023855.
